components.label: HTML
components.content:
Finance Department
Business Licensing Division
1 Centennial Square
Victoria BC V8W 1P6

components.label: HTML
components.content: Application must be completed in full. For information, or assistance completing this form, please contact Business Licensing Services 250.361.0572 ext.1 or by email at businesslicence@victoria.ca. You can mail your completed application to the above address. Please be advised this document is subject to the Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act and access can be requested.

components.title: Business Information
components.label: Business Information
Mailing Address if different from Business Address

components.title: Business structure Information
components.label: Business structure Information
1.a Sole Proprietors Name
components.tooltip: If you plan to operate a business on your own, either under a business name or your own name

components.label: 1.a Partnership Name(s)
components.tooltip: If you plan to operate the business with one or more partners

components.label: 1.a Limited / Incorporated Company Name
components.tooltip: If you plan to operate the business as a separate legal entity, separate from yourself and your personal assets

components.label: 2. Is this a Home based business?
2.a Will you be receiving clients at your residence?
2.b How many clients on average do you receive per day?

components.html: Home Occupation refers to the making, servicing, or repairing goods and the provision of services for hire from a residence. To qualify for a Home Based Business Licence the applicant must reside at the location they are applying for, be the only person engaged in the business and comply with the Home Occupation Bylaw No.84-44 Schedule D – Zoning Regulation Bylaw No.80
components.label: Content
3. Do you need Inter-Municipal Licence?
components.tooltip: This will allow you to work within all 13 municipal boundaries

components.html: Businesses in a variety of mobile trades (e.g. caterers, contractors, towing services) can purchase a business licence that is honoured throughout Greater Victoria. Applicants must purchase this licence from the municipality in which their business office is located, either your home or a commercial location.
components.label: Content
4. Is Building Permit Required ?
components.tooltip:
(Will you be making any alterations to the premises or changing the use of the premise)
Ex: Office to Retail

components.content:
Checklist for applicant:
  • Application signed and completed in full
  • Documents attached (Incorporation/Certification/Share Purchase Agreement) (if applicable)
  • Detailed Site Plan/Layout of Business provided (if applicable)
  • Occupant Load/Floor Plans of Building (if applicable)
